A Venn diagram is a graphical representation of sets or groups using circles or other shapes. It is used to illustrate the relationships and similarities between different sets of elements. 
The diagram consists of overlapping circles or shapes, with each circle representing a set and the overlapping regions showing the elements that belong to multiple sets.

